humanMachineDialogue.author: Memory Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: According to the report, there are 7 lymph nodes examined, and 2 of them are positive for metastatic carcinoma. This corresponds to the N1 stage as per the AJCC staging system (New Rule 12: N1 indicates metastases in 1 to 3 axillary lymph nodes).

humanMachineDialogue.author: ZS Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: The patient has 2 out of 7 axillary lymph nodes with metastasis, with the largest metastatic focus being 0.7 cm. This corresponds to a pathologic N stage of N1a.
